   "source": [
    "# Experiment Simulation Weights"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyAdasi.sim_utils import GenderSystem, Gender, Chromo, generate_gender_func, apg, dist_inverse, generate_distribution_func, get_reverse_index\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "system = GenderSystem(False, Chromo.X, Chromo.Y, Chromo.O, extended=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "determine_gender = generate_gender_func(system)\n",
    "distribution_func = generate_distribution_func(system)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{OO: {(OO, OO): 4, (OO, OY): 2, (OO, OX): 2, (OY, OX): 1, (OX, OX): 1},\n",
       " OY: {(OO, OY): 2,\n",
       "  (OO, YY): 4,\n",
       "  (OO, YX): 2,\n",
       "  (OY, YX): 1,\n",
       "  (OY, OX): 1,\n",
       "  (YY, OX): 2,\n",
       "  (YX, OX): 1},\n",
       " YY: {(OY, YX): 1, (YY, YX): 2, (YX, YX): 1},\n",
       " YX: {(OY, YX): 1,\n",
       "  (OY, XX): 2,\n",
       "  (OY, OX): 1,\n",
       "  (YY, YX): 2,\n",
       "  (YY, XX): 4,\n",
       "  (YY, OX): 2,\n",
       "  (YX, YX): 2,\n",
       "  (YX, XX): 2,\n",
       "  (YX, OX): 1},\n",
       " XX: {(YX, YX): 1,\n",
       "  (YX, XX): 2,\n",
       "  (YX, OX): 1,\n",
       "  (XX, XX): 4,\n",
       "  (XX, OX): 2,\n",
       "  (OX, OX): 1},\n",
       " OX: {(OO, YX): 2,\n",
       "  (OO, XX): 4,\n",
       "  (OO, OX): 2,\n",
       "  (OY, YX): 1,\n",
       "  (OY, XX): 2,\n",
       "  (OY, OX): 1,\n",
       "  (YX, OX): 1,\n",
       "  (XX, OX): 2,\n",
       "  (OX, OX): 2}}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "get_reverse_index(system)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "input_prob = np.array([[0.5], [0], [0.35], [0], [0.15], [0]])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = np.ndarray((0, 8))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pos_values = np.arange(0, 1.05, 0.05).round(2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "results = np.ndarray((0, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "for a in pos_values:\n",
    "\tfor b in pos_values:\n",
    "\t\tcurr = input_prob.copy()\n",
    "\t\tprev = curr.copy()\n",
    "\t\tcurr = distribution_func(prev)\n",
    "\t\t\n",
    "\t\tfor i in range(2, 51):\n",
    "\t\t\taterm = distribution_func(curr)\n",
    "\t\t\tbterm = distribution_func(prev)\n",
    "\t\t\tcterm = dist_inverse(bterm)\n",
    "\t\t\tnext = a * aterm + (1 - a) * b * bterm + (1 - a) * (1 - b) * cterm\n",
    "\t\t\t# next = a * aterm + (1 - a) * bterm\n",
    "\t\t\tprev = curr\n",
    "\t\t\tcurr = next\n",
    "\t\t\n",
    "\t\tresults = np.vstack((results, np.hstack((np.array([a, b]), curr.T[0]))))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "l = [\"a\", \"b\"]\n",
    "l.extend(apg)\n",
    "pdf = pd.DataFrame(results, columns = l)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pdf[Gender.D] = [0] * len(pdf)\n",
    "pdf[Gender.E] = [0] * len(pdf)\n",
    "pdf[Gender.A] = [0] * len(pdf)\n",
    "\n",
    "for g in apg:\n",
    "    pdf[determine_gender(g)] += pdf[g]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[OO, OY, YY, YX, XX, OX]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "apg"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "gene_maps = {}\n",
    "gender_maps = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for g in apg:\n",
    "    gene_maps[g] = np.array(pdf[g]).reshape(len(pos_values), len(pos_values))\n",
    "\n",
    "for r in [Gender.D, Gender.E, Gender.A]:\n",
    "    gender_maps[r] = np.array(pdf[r]).reshape(len(pos_values), len(pos_values))"
   ]
  },

   "metadata": {},

    "\n",
    "axs = axs.reshape(-1)\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(len(apg)):\n",
    "    axs[i].imshow(gene_maps[apg[i]])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    axs[i].set_xticks(np.arange(len(pos_values)), labels=pos_values)\n",
    "    axs[i].set_yticks(np.arange(len(pos_values)), labels=pos_values)\n",
    "\n",
    "    axs[i].set_xlabel(\"b\")\n",

    "    \n",

   ]
